Her case study explores how industrial capitalism fueled campuses of the auto industry.

name: The Projects: A New History of Public Housing
description: In his new book The Projects, Howard A. Husock explains how the US struggles to provide affordable housing, detailing the tragic rise and fall of public housing and the pitfalls of other subsidy programs. He takes us inside a progressive movement led by New York City philanthropists, politicians, and business magnates who first championed public housing.

name: The Wrigley Building: The Making of an Icon

name: Cheating on Harold: The Spokane, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: When you think "UCB improv" you think of the Harold but what if UCB's house team improvisers decided to cheat??? This week, they're cheating on Harold with.... the Spokane in a show you won't want to miss!

name: ASSSCAT NY, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: ASSSSCAT is UCB's signature improv show that has played to critical acclaim and sold out audiences across the country. It starts with a group of improv comedians from film & TV taking the stage with a special guest monologist.

name: What I Did For Love
description: You tell us about your love life and we'll do improv all about it! One of UCB's longest running weekend improv teams is back! Catch them while you can for a wild and wonderful night of improv.

name: The Great American Shit Carnival: Magnus' Torment
description: A torrid celebration of all that is wrong and unholy. You truly have no idea how low we can go. The rotting corpse of PT Barnum has been reanimated to bring you the most perverse, exploitative and disgusting version of the Greatest Show on Earth.

name: What the Hell? An Incredible Improv Show, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: No gimmicks, this is a great improv show where talented performers do what they love -- improv! We're combining veteran performers and up-and-comers to put on an incredible improv show.

name: Hoopty: Ride or Die, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: A fiery comedy car crash with precision chaos. A high-octane improv show that's barely street legal. Running on instinct, speed, and just the right amount of stupidity, this show won't pass inspection, but it will leave you laughing.

name: The Diversity Jam

name: Baby Wants Candy, The Fully Improvised Musical, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: World famous, fully improvised musical. The audience shouts out the title of a musical that has never been performed before. Baby Wants Candy then creates that musical on the spot.

name: Sketch Cage Match, Live and LIVESTREAMED!

name: SPANK: Please Don't F*ck the Funny Out of Me
description: Brand-new shows auditioning to be UCB shows. Brand-new sketch and solo shows will be birthed right before your very eyes in a bid to run at UCB! Will these scrappy new shows make the cut?

name: MAUDE NIGHT: Ponyboy & 11:11, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: Maude Night boasts brand new material by UCB's house sketch teams every month. Come see top-notch sketch comedy featuring two teams of UCB's finest writers and performers.

name: Late Night & Friends, Live and LIVESTREAMED!

name: Teacher Feature, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: UCB Teachers improvise for you! UCB Teachers Donald Chang, Ray Cordova, and Molly Thomas host a group of UCB Teachers who'll improvise for you. Prepare to have your minds blown as these vets prove they can walk the walk.

name: BETTY NIGHT: The Best of The Roster, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: Come see the twisted geniuses of UCB's character house teams! Betty Night showcases brand-new solo characters every month by a team of UCB's finest writer/performers.

name: The Conductor, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: A beloved orchestra conductor with an "unusual" style spirals into madness after discovering the dark truth behind his brilliance. (It's a comedy I swear) Amadeo Fusca's Absurd/Clown comedy hour 'The Conductor' is fresh off performances at NY Comedy Festival, Edinburgh Fringe Festival and UCB LA.

name: Siblings Playdate: 50th Show Special
description: It's a 50-show celebration! Siblings celebrates performing 50 shows with, you guessed it, more improv!! Playdate is the ultimate melting pot of New York's funniest, richest, and most attractive improvisers (unverified).

name: UCB Training Center Presents: The Living Room, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: Sit down and relax --- we're bringing the living room to the stage (literally). This advanced improv class dives into The Living Room form, a Chicago favorite that starts with real-life stories, flows into scene work, and continues to transition back and forth.

name: John and Scott: Two Person Improv
description: Two Friends, One 1-Hour Show. Scott Adsit (30 Rock, Big Hero 6) and John Lutz (30 Rock, Late Night with Seth Meyers) have been improvising together in New York since 2010 and would love for you to come watch!!

name: It's been a year?!?, Live and LIVESTREAMED!

name: Cage Match: TBD vs. Overthinking , Live and LIVESTREAMED!

name: Duchovny, Live and LIVESTREAMED!

name: The Foundation, Live and LIVESTREAMED!
description: THE FOUNDATION, one of New York City's oldest and most storied comedy teams, sees it as our duty to not only have a few laughs, but to change the world through sketch comedy. This month we are proud to form THE FOUNDATION... TO DETERMINE THE SONG OF THE SUMMER, an hour of characters, good sketches, and great music.

name: clint SLOP, Live and LIVESTREAMED!

name: The Magical City: George Morrison's New York
description: An exhibition showcasing the work of George Morrison, exploring his journey from a remote Native American village to becoming a significant artist. The exhibition highlights his overcoming of numerous challenges throughout his life and career.

name: Urban Stomp: Dreams & Defiance on the Dance Floor
location: Museum of the City of New York
description: This exhibition celebrates New York City's diverse dance cultures, tracing over 200 years of social dance from the 19th century to the present day. It explores the creativity and joy found in various dance forms across the city.

name: 100: A Century of Collections, Community, and Creativity
location: Schomburg Center for Research in Black Culture
description: An exhibition offering a glimpse into the Schomburg Center's collections, celebrating 100 years of its contributions to collections, community, and creativity. Visitors will experience the sights, sounds, and objects that have defined the institution.

name: Superfine: Tailoring Black Style
description: This exhibition examines Black style over three centuries through the lens of dandyism, exploring its cultural and historical significance. It delves into the evolution of Black fashion and its connection to broader societal changes.

name: P. S. Art 2025: Celebrating the Creative Spirit of New York City Kids
description: An annual exhibition showcasing the artistic achievements of New York City public school students and their teachers. This year marks the 23rd anniversary of P.S. Art, featuring 137 selected works.

name: A Century of The New Yorker
description: This major exhibition from The New York Public Library celebrates 100 years of The New Yorker magazine. It draws on the library's extensive archives and contributors' papers to bring the magazine's history to life.

name: Museum of the City of New York Unveils New Section of Activist New York: "Housing Activism: Rent Strikes and Tenant Mobilizations, 1908-1939"
location: Museum of the City of New York
description: A new section of the "Activist New York" exhibition focuses on the history of tenant organizing in the city, highlighting rent strikes and mobilizations from 1908 to 1939. It explores the grassroots efforts that shaped housing in New York City.

name: Rashid Johnson: A Poem for Deep Thinkers
description: This major solo exhibition features the diverse body of work by artist Rashid Johnson, spanning nearly 30 years. It highlights his engagement with history, philosophy, literature, and music, and his role as a creative force.

name: Projects: Ufuoma Essi
description: An exhibition by artist Ufuoma Essi, who explores how history is carried in the body and challenges official narratives. The exhibition focuses on re-centering marginalized Black life experiences within historical accounts.

name: Face Value: Celebrity Press Photography
description: An exhibition examining the 20th-century Hollywood star system through celebrity press photography. It explores how studio-produced images were manipulated for public consumption before the digital age.

name: Breaking the Mold: Brooklyn Museum at 200
description: Celebrating its 200th anniversary, the Brooklyn Museum presents "Breaking the Mold," an exhibition highlighting its collection's legacy of championing imaginative and conversation-starting artworks. It comprises three chapters that showcase the museum's unique history.

name: Blacklisted: An American Story
description: This exhibition explores the intersection of politics, art, commerce, and social dynamics during Hollywood's Red Scare. Through photographs, objects, and film, it reveals personal narratives and different perspectives on American patriotism.
